<br>
The Doshas, Pitta, Vata, and Kapha are all part of us, not just one or the other.  Each of us contain all three to live, Pitta controls our metabolism, intake of air, and intake of food.  Vata Controls Movement, Movement ranging from anything, from blood to nerve impluses.  And Kapha controls structure, structure as in cell structure, muscle, fat, and bone.  <br>
<br>
To live we need all three of these in our body.  So this gets going into a little I guess you can call it a quiz. You answer 60 questions, 20 per Dosha. After you take the quiz, I can explain what dosha you are.<br>
<br>
Okay, some other facts.  I am in Psychology 205 International class, So basically thats a class that used extra funding to learn all about eastern/older Psychological methods/healing methods.  This princple is 5,000 to 6,000 years old so its been around for awhile, and since our class has taken this test it is extremly accurate in finding out your body type.<br>
<br>
I will explain the body types another day, for today I will post up this quiz so you all can take it. Now this is purely out of interest, I find this way of perverting diseases, finding your body type, and overall view of your personal life on this fasinating.  So no, I'm not here to say take this quiz cause you have to, just take it if your curious to find out your body type and how you should help improve the way your live, your surroundings, and your overall view on life.<br>
<br>
I believe I stated everything I needed, so let me go on to explain this quiz.  As I stated earlier, its 20 questions per Quiz, three dosha so 60 questions total.  For each question its a 1-6 scale,  1 being Does not apply, 3 being Applies sometimes, and 6 being applies most of the time.  To help your choice in 1-6 scale, Remember this, For fairly objective physical traits, your choice will usually be obvious.  For mental Traits and behaviour, which are more subjective, you should answer according to how you have felt and acted most of your life, or at least for the past few years.<br>
<br>
Also, when your done with the questions, Add up total score for Vata quiz, than the Pitta quiz, than the Kapha quiz, and either post your total scores up or hold out till I post up the different types.  Now, I myself is still learning this so I'm not a Ayurveda Doctor.  But I do know enough to give you accurate list of your body type.<br>
<br>
Vata Quiz, 20 questions, 1-6 scale.<br>
1. I perform activity very quickly.<br>
2. I am not good at memorizing things and than remembering them later.<br>
3. I am enthusiastic and vivacious by nature.<br>
4. I have a thin physique--I don't gain weight very easily.<br>
5. I have always learned new things very quickly.<br>
6. My characteristic gait while walking is light and quick.<br>
7. I tend to have difficulty making decisions.<br>
8. I tend to develop gas or become constipated easily.<br>
9. I tend to have cold hands and feet.<br>
10. I become anxious or worried frequently.<br>
11. I don't tolerate cold weather as well as most people.<br>
12. I speak quickly and my friends think I am talkative.<br>
13. My moods change easily and I am somewhat emotional by nature.<br>
14. I often have difficulty in falling asleep or having a sound night's sleep.<br>
15. My skin tends to be very dry, especially in the winter.<br>
16. My mind is very active, sometimes restless, but also very imaginative.<br>
17. My movements are quick and active; my energy tends to come in bursts.<br>
18. I am easily excitable.<br>
19. Left on my own, my eating and sleeping habits tend to be irregular.<br>
20. I learn quickly, but I also forget quickly.<br>
